    "description": "We at Piramal Pharma Global Group are looking for an experienced Consultant Physician based out of Nashik. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Piramal Pharma Global Group:\nPiramal Pharma Global Group is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Chartered Accountant (ICAI)\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Nashik, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Piramal Pharma Global Group!",
